@startuml component_architecture
!theme plain

title UIM SAP Identity Provisioning (IP) - Component Architecture

actor "Administrators" as Admin
actor "Scheduler / CI" as Scheduler

node "Identity Provisioning Service Runtime" {
  component "IPServer\n(vibe.d REST API)" as Api
  component "IPService\n(Provisioning Engine +\nCRUD + Notifications)" as Domain
  database "IPStore\n(In-Memory Data)" as Store
}

cloud "Source Systems\n(SAP IAS, SCIM, LDAP…)" as Src
cloud "Target Systems\n(Azure AD, SCIM, LDAP…)" as Tgt

Admin --> Api : register systems,\ndefine transformations,\nsubscribe to notifications
Scheduler --> Api : trigger provisioning\njobs (full/delta)
Api --> Domain : routed use-case operations
Domain --> Store : persist/retrieve\nentity data

Domain ..> Src : read users & groups\n(simulated in-memory)
Domain ..> Tgt : write provisioned entities\n(simulated in-memory)

note right of Domain
Capabilities:
- Source / target / proxy systems
- User & group provisioning
- Transformation & filter rules
- Full and delta read modes
- Job execution with counters
- Job logging (info/warning/error)
- Notification subscriptions
- Tenant-scoped multitenancy
- Dashboard analytics
end note

@enduml
